avakāśa (Ep. Ind., Vol. IV, p. 347, note 5), ‘opportunity <BR>for a grammatical rule taking effect’.

अवलगा
avalagā (LP), same as Gujarātī oḻaga; cf. <BR>avalagā sad = aiv = āvalokyā (LP), ‘care should be constantly <BR>taken’.

