avani-vetana (SITI), police duties of a village;<BR>contri<BR>bution for such duties;<BR>the same as Tamil pā ṭikāval.

आवर
āvara (CII 4), a stall. Cf. āvāra.

आवार
āvāra (IE 8-5), cf. āpaṇeṣu āvāraḥ, ‘collections to be <BR>made from the shops in a market’. Cf. āvara.

अवराधिक
avar-ādhika (CII 1), ‘more or less’.

अवरज
avaraja (ML), a younger brother or cousin.

आवरण
āvaraṇa (EI 17), a shield. <BR>(SITI), shelter, covering;<BR>same as prākāra or wall around <BR>the temple.

आवर्जनीय
āvarjanīya (LP), ‘to be received’.

अवरोधन
avarodhana (CII 1), household;<BR>cf. antaḥpura.

