Āvasathika (IE 8-3), variously explained as ‘the superin<BR>tendent of avasathas, i. e. colleges or dharma-śālās’, ‘the super<BR>visor of the royal palace and other government buildings’ <BR>(Hist. Beng., I, ed. Majumdar, p. 284);<BR>‘one who keeps the <BR>domestic fire (āvasathya) burning with daily offerings’ <BR>(D. Bhattacharya, Halāyudha's Brāhmaṇasarvasva, p. xx);<BR>etc. <BR>(EI 9, 11, 24), title or family name of Brāhmaṇas. Cf. <BR>Āvasathin.

