Balādhikṛta (CII 3, 4;<BR>BL;<BR>HD), ‘the commander of <BR>an army’. See JBBRAS, Vol. XVI, p. 108 (Balādhikṛta <BR>following Senāpati);<BR>Kādambarī, para. 74. According to some <BR>(cf. Balādhi in LP), the Balādhikṛta was probably the head <BR>of a territorial unit like the present Māmlatdār. See <BR>Balādhipa.

