balīvarda, cf. a-paramparā-balīvarda, etc. (IE 8-5);<BR>a <BR>pair of bullocks (which the villagers were obliged to provide <BR>for the cart of the royal officers when they camped or toured <BR>in their villages). See also vara-balīvarda.

बाण
bāṇa (IE 7-1-2;<BR>EI 25), ‘five’.

बानसवेर्गडे
Bānasa-vĕrgaḍĕ (599-11-2), variant spelling of Kannaḍa <BR>Bhānasa-vĕrgaḍĕ (q. v.).

बन्ध
bandha (EI 31), a dam or highway.

बन्धदण्ड
bandha-daṇḍa (IE 8-5;<BR>EI 12, 33), probably, ransom or <BR>fine in lieu of imprisonment.

