Jenā (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXVIII, p. 304), Oḏiyā;<BR>‘a prince’;<BR>a title of nobility;<BR>later stereotyped as a family name in Orissa.

झम्पिन्
jhampin (EI 12), ‘excelling’.

झाट
jhāṭa (Ep. Ind., Vol. V, p. 183), a shrub, wood or thicket;<BR>Bengali jhāḏ;<BR>a bush;<BR>used in sa-jhāṭa-viṭapa (EI 27).

