Khshāyathiya vazrka (IE 8-2), Old Persian;<BR>‘the great <BR>king’;<BR>royal title. It was translated by the Indo-Greek kings <BR>in Greek and Prakrit in the legend of their coins and was the <BR>original of the Indian royal title Mahārāja. See Basilĕos <BR>Mĕgalŏu.

किल
kila, cf. Paṭṭakila, Veṭakila.

कीलक
kīlaka (EI 23), a peg [for marking boundaries].

