Māṇḍavī (LP), one who gets the market-tax;<BR>same as <BR>Māṇḍapika. <BR>(LP), a tax levied on articles that are to be sold in a <BR>market-place. <BR>(IE 8-3), Marāṭhī;<BR>same as maṇḍapikā, ‘customs house’.

