māṅgalīyaka (LP), probably, a tax collected on the occa<BR>sion of auspicious events in the royal family, such as the birth <BR>of a son to the king.

माङ्गल्य
māṅgalya (SITI), Tamil maṅgiliyam; the ornament called <BR>tāli worn round the neck as the marriage badge by a married <BR>woman with her husband living.

मङ्गणि
