māṇikya-bhāṇḍāra, cf. maṇikka-paṇḍāram-kāppār (SITI), ‘keeper <BR>of the treasury [of precious stones] in the temple or palace.’

मानिन्
Mānin, cf. Māṇi (IA 18), an Elder.

मानित
mānita (LP), accepted.

