Manneya (CITD), Telugu;<BR>same as Sanskrit Mānya; a <BR>respectable man;<BR>a chieftain;<BR>a commander;<BR>a chief. Cf. <BR>Mannīḍu, Manniya. <BR>(SII 11-1), ruler of a group of villages;<BR>cf. manneya- <BR>svāmya, tenure held by a Manneya.

