mārgaṇaka (EI 3;<BR>IA 18;<BR>CII 4;<BR>HRS), known from re<BR>cords like those of the Caulukyas;<BR>a levy;<BR>a kind of cess or tax;<BR>explained as ‘benevolences of a general character, as distin<BR>guished from the special types called prasthaka and skandhaka’. <BR>See mārgaṇika.

