parivastra, cf. Tamil parivaṭṭam, pariśaṭṭam, pariyaṭṭam (SITI), <BR>literally, garment;<BR>honour done to a nobleman in a temple by <BR>tying a piece of cloth (generally, silk cloth) round his head.

