pārśva (HRS), extra charge upon land over and above <BR>the king's grain-share, which was a branch of ‘accidental re<BR>venue’ according to the Arthaśāstra. See Ghoshal, H. Rev. <BR>Syst., pp. 28, 38. <BR>(IE 8-4), explained by some as a small territorial unit;<BR>but may be ‘side’;<BR>cf. prāveśya.

