Pārśvika (EI 9;<BR>CII 4), an aide-de-camp;<BR>also used to in<BR>dicate a neighbour or one having land in the neighbourhood <BR>of the gift land (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXXIII, p. 197, text line 13).

पर्ताब्
partāb (SII 1), Sanskrit pratāpa; a half pagoda.

पर्वमासोत्सव
parva-mās-otsava (EI 15), a festival.

पारुत्थ
pāruttha, a silver coin equal to 8 drammas of copper or billon <BR>(JNSI, Vol. XXII, p. 196).

पर्वन्
