पट्टशाल
paṭṭa-śāla (CITD), Sanskrit ºśālā; a reading hall;<BR>probably, <BR>‘the main hall’;<BR>in Kannaḍa, ‘a silk-shop’. <BR>(EI 3), name applied to the abode of certain Brāhmaṇas. <BR>(LP), cf. Gujaratī Paḍaśāla; the first room in a house.

