पातुसाह
Pātusāha (BL), Indian modification of a Muslim imperial <BR>title;<BR>same as Persian Pādshāh.

पट्वारि
Paṭvāri (IE 8-3), probably Sanskrit Paṭṭavārika; the <BR>accountant-clerk;<BR>a member of the administrative board called <BR>Cauthiyā in Western India.

