Paura-vīthillaka, probably officers in charge of a city and <BR>a subdivision;<BR>cf. Paura-vi(vī)thillaka-grāmakūṭa-niyuktāniyukta- <BR>pradhān-āpradhāna (Ep. Ind., Vol. XXV, p. 169, where the <BR>reading is given as visvillaka).

