Piśunavetrika (EI 33;<BR>HD), probably, an officer who drives <BR>away undesirable persons with a cane;<BR>or, one engaged in a <BR>court for caning culprits. See Ep. Ind., Vol. XI, p. 94. See <BR>Vetrika, Yāṣṭika, Veṭakila.

पिटक
piṭaka (CII 4), a measure of capacity. <BR>Cf. Traipiṭaka.

पितलहार
Pitalahāra (EI 20, 32), a brazier.

