Pīṭhikāvitta (IE 8-3;<BR>EI 12;<BR>HD), probably, ‘those who <BR>have acquired [special] seats’;<BR>same as Utthitāsanika. The <BR>word occurs in such records as the Belava plate of Bhojavarma<BR>deva (Ep. Ind., Vol. XII, p. 40). Cf. Velāvitta. Pīṭhikāvitta <BR>is sometimes explained as the collector of state dues from pil<BR>grims or religious institutions (Sen, Hist. Asp. Ins. Beng., p. 552).

