sādhana (IE 8-3;<BR>EI 24;<BR>LP), an army, cf. sādhana-sahasra- <BR>aikam, an army consisting of one thousand men. <BR>(EI 15), an army, or money. <BR>(SII 12), cf. mūla-sādhana, the original deed;<BR>also called <BR>mūla-olai in Tamil.

